# Python Conventions

## Required

- Type hints on all functions and tool parameters (`str | None`, `list[dict]`, `Literal` for enums)
- All I/O is `async`; use `asyncio.gather` for parallel API calls
- Use `uv` for dependencies — never `pip` directly

## Imports

Match package import style:

```python
from polymarket_mcp.config import Settings
from polymarket_mcp.utils.helpers import err, get, text
from polymarket_mcp.utils.formatters import format_search_markets
```

## Naming

- Functions/tools: `snake_case` (`get_user_positions`)
- Types: `PascalCase` (`Settings`, `Category`)
- MCP tool name matches function name

## HTTP Params

Filter `None` values before API calls — do not send null query params:

```python
params = {"q": query, "events_status": "active" if active_only else None}
data = await get(url, params=params)  # helpers filters None
```

## Scope

- Keep changes minimal and focused
- Match surrounding code style; no over-abstraction
- Add comments only for non-obvious business logic
